"'''Hunting the Hunters'''" is a short story published in [[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine 6|''Star Wars Galaxy Magazine'' 6]], and later on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]]. It was written by [[Bill Smith]] and illustrated by [[Omaha Pérez]].

==Plot summary==
[[Andov Syn|Nariss Siv Loqesh]] apprehends a [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] quarry when his expeditor, a [[Bimm/Legends|Bimm]] named [[Crote (Bimm)|Crote]], receives word that the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] has invited Loqesh to join the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] hired to track down the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]. Loqesh declines – he doesn’t do work for the Empire – and goes into hiding to avoid Imperial reprisal.

==Continuity==
The brief story suggested that it took place on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Garnib]] without explicitly stating so, but [[Tav Breil'lya|Breil'lya]] commented that the planet is very hot – which is not a characteristic of frigid Garnib.<ref name="TERC" />

